cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.MM, cs.DS 

This paper deals with channel state information (CSI) feedback delay and its impact on interference management in communication systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory), which deals with the fundamental limits of communication systems. The paper also discusses wireless channels, which makes cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) a likely category as well. The proposed transmission method involves space-time interference alignment, which falls under cs.SI (Signal Processing) and cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper presents a trade-off between CSI feedback delay and degrees of freedom (DoF) gain, which can be analyzed using techniques from cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
